{"text": "Late-onset scleroderma renal crisis induced by tacrolimus and prednisolone: a case report. Scleroderma renal crisis (SRC) is a rare complication of systemic sclerosis (SSc) but can be severe enough to require temporary or permanent renal replacement therapy. Moderate to high dose corticosteroid use is recognized as a major risk factor for SRC. Furthermore, there have been reports of thrombotic microangiopathy precipitated by cyclosporine in patients with SSc. In this article, we report a patient with SRC induced by tacrolimus and corticosteroids. The aim of this work is to call attention to the risk of tacrolimus use in patients with SSc.", "sourcedb": "PubMed", "sourceid": "22836123", "denotations": [{"id": "T1", "span": {"begin": 11, "end": 35}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T2", "span": {"begin": 47, "end": 57}, "obj": "ChemicalEntity"}, {"id": "T3", "span": {"begin": 62, "end": 74}, "obj": "ChemicalEntity"}, {"id": "T4", "span": {"begin": 91, "end": 115}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T5", "span": {"begin": 117, "end": 120}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T6", "span": {"begin": 148, "end": 166}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T7", "span": {"begin": 168, "end": 171}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T8", "span": {"begin": 281, "end": 295}, "obj": "ChemicalEntity"}, {"id": "T9", "span": {"begin": 341, "end": 344}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T10", "span": {"begin": 386, "end": 412}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T11", "span": {"begin": 429, "end": 441}, "obj": "ChemicalEntity"}, {"id": "T12", "span": {"begin": 445, "end": 453}, "obj": "OrganismTaxon"}, {"id": "T13", "span": {"begin": 459, "end": 462}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T14", "span": {"begin": 493, "end": 500}, "obj": "OrganismTaxon"}, {"id": "T15", "span": {"begin": 506, "end": 509}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T16", "span": {"begin": 521, "end": 531},